di-netboot-assistant (0.37) unstable; urgency=low

  * DHCP configuration changed: PXELinux option 210 (pathprefix) isn't
    needed anymore. Previously, one had to configure the DHCP to send 
    option 210="/". This isn't required anymore, thanks to PXELinux>3.55
    which supports "::" filename prefix to force absolute filename.

 -- Frank Lin PIAT <fpiat@klabs.be>  Thu, 15 Oct 2009 09:23:35 +0200
